    "apply_url": "https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/savvy/41dabf52-d665-4c67-a2ae-31f70df6c470/application",
    "company": "Savvy Wealth",
    "compensation": "",
    "content_hash": "941189b3b151ab2a",
    "department": "R\u0026D",
    "description": "ABOUT SAVVY WEALTH:\n\nWealth management is a $545 billion industry in the US, yet remains archaic and inefficient with low technology penetration. 75% of financial advisors don’t offer digital communication beyond email, and 62% still build financial plans manually in Excel. This leads to a poor client experience and results in financial advisors spending over 70% of their time on non-client facing, manual work.\n\nSavvy is changing that. We’re building the most advisor-centric platform in wealth management: a digital-first solution that modernizes human financial advice. Advisors who partner with Savvy tap into AI-powered software, automated sales and marketing, and seamless back office workflows to scale faster and spend more time with clients.\n\nWe’ve raised over $105M to date from Thrive Capital, Index Ventures, Canvas Ventures, Mark Casady (former LPL Financial CEO), and other top-tier investors. Our team is made up of repeat founders and operators who’ve helped build Airbnb, Square, Brex, Carta, Facebook, $200B+ RIAs, and more.\n\nSavvy is at a pivotal point in its growth trajectory, having established strong product-market fit in providing a modern platform to financial advisors. We’ve surpassed $5.1 billion in AUM in less than three years, grown 600%+ in the last 18 months, and are entering the next phase of the company which involves rapid expansion of our product offering and continued revenue growth. Come help us scale!\n\n\nRESPONSIBILITIES\n\n - Build AI-powered product features for advisors and Savvy operations teams (e.g., copilots, skilled agents, automations, summarization, routing, extraction, recommendations), with a bias toward shipping quickly\n\n - Rapidly prototype and deliver using modern AI tooling (e.g., Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Cursor, Devin, etc.) while maintaining high engineering standards - from using individual tools to get work done all the way up to leveraging a complex orchestration layer to string together a dozen tools to get things done even faster\n\n - Own the end-to-end product development lifecycle - identify opportunities, design solutions, ship to production, and iterate\n\n - Produce production-grade, readable, maintainable code with good testing discipline\n\n - Partner tightly with Product, Design, Data, and business stakeholders to define scope, de-risk execution, and deliver high-impact outcomes\n\n - Work directly with our customers (financial advisors) to learn their workflows and needs directly from the source\n\n - Run fast!\n\n\nLEVEL-SPECIFIC EXPECTATIONS\n\n\nMID-LEVEL\n\n - Implement AI workflows using established patterns (prompting, tool/function calling, retrieval, evals) and improve over time\n\n - Ship well-scoped features independently; break ambiguous problems into concrete tasks\n\n - Contribute to code quality via reviews, tests, and documentation across your team\n\n\nSENIOR\n\n - Build Savvy AI systems (RAG, classification/extraction pipelines, agentic workflows)\n\n - Establish team patterns for rapid AI development (prompt/versioning strats, eval harnesses (ours and/or with vendors), rollouts, observability, testing)\n\n - Lead projects (medium to large) end-to-end\n\n - Mentor others on best practices as they emerge\n\n\nSTAFF\n\n - Set technical direction for applied AI across multiple product areas\n\n - Drive roadmap shaping with Engineering/Product/Design/Leadership (including CxO leadership)\n\n - Define platform primitives for AI development (shared tooling, libraries, evaluation frameworks, guardrails, cost/perf opts)\n\n - Raise the bar org-wide, even beyond the reach of engineering\n\n\nMUST HAVE:\n\n - You’re in AI tools day and night, tinkering on work projects as well as personal\n\n - You've built scaling web applications with obvious business impact\n\n - System design expertise as it applies to emerging AI software development trends, for example, system designs that maximize the use of context windows with strong separation between components\n\n - Full-stack proficiency (or evidence you can cover your gaps via AI tools)\n   \n   - We use Rails; React; Next, Postgres, GraphQL\n\n - Proven collaboration abilities in cross-functional startup environments with mentoring experience and strong technical communication skills\n\n\nNICE TO HAVE:\n\n - Fintech domain knowledge including financial services, wealth management, regulatory compliance, or financial data integrations\n\n - Modern development ecosystem experience with macOS toolchains, CI/CD pipelines, IaaS providers, and observability platforms (eg, Datadog)\n\n\nBENEFITS:\n\n - Competitive salary and equity package\n\n - Unlimited PTO + paid company holidays\n\n - Access to holistic medical, dental, and vision plans\n\n - Company 401(k), Commuter, and HSA/FSA plans\n\n - NYC office in the heart of Manhattan\n\n - Lunch and snacks provided in the office\n\n - Access to virtual mental health care (Spring Health), vision related benefits (XP Health), and health concierge (Rightway) to help you find the right care\n\n - Access to counseling for stress management, dependent care, nutrition, fitness, legal, and financial issues (Guardian WorkLifeMatters EAP)",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
